Evensong / CCR — Dual License
==============================

This repository is dual-licensed under two distinct licenses that apply to
different parts of the project. See **LICENSING.md** for the definitive
directory-by-directory mapping.

    +---------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
    | Part of repository                                | Applicable license     |
    +---------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
    | Source code, tests, benchmark harness, scripts,   | Apache License 2.0     |
    | packages, configs (src/, packages/, scripts/,     | (LICENSE-APACHE)       |
    | benchmarks/, tests/, services/, api/, shared/,    |                        |
    | skills/, *.json, *.toml, *.lock, *.ts, *.tsx)     |                        |
    +---------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
    | Research artifacts, paper drafts, long-form       | CC BY-NC-ND 4.0        |
    | research docs, anything marked under              | (LICENSE-CC-BY-NC-ND)  |
    | docs/research/ or NOTICE'd as research-only       |                        |
    +---------------------------------------------------+------------------------+
    | Everything else (developer docs, READMEs,         | Apache License 2.0     |
    | CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, etc.)      | (LICENSE-APACHE)       |
    +---------------------------------------------------+------------------------+

This dual-licensing model is intentional: the CODE is meant to be reusable
by other open-source projects under a permissive Apache 2.0 grant (patent
license included), while RESEARCH DELIVERABLES (paper text, novel experimental
narratives, etc.) retain attribution-only / non-commercial / no-derivatives
protections so they cannot be scraped into commercial training corpora or
rewritten without credit.

